A British teenager has died on holiday in Ibiza. The 19-year-old man was pulled from a swimming pool in the early hours of Sunday, but he was pronounced dead at the scene. A spokesperson for local emergency services said the teenager had suffered a cardiac arrest and did not respond to CPR treatment. An investigation is under way to determine whether the man was intoxicated at his time of death. A Foreign Office spokesman said: “We are providing assistance to the family of a British man who died on 8 July in Ibiza, and are in contact with the Spanish authorities.”